Description: Personal fundraising platform like GoFundMe for the unserved West-African region.
Full Description: RaiseMeFunds is a crowdfunding platform that allows members of the community to raise funds for events ranging from celebrations and graduations to life tragedy in French-speaking African countries.    Overview of Business   RaiseMeFunds empowers individuals to raise capital in a secure and affordable channel for all in this part of the world.   Problem   People in need in French West African countries have used social media platforms to ask for help for tragedies relief for the most part but donors in Africa and abroad are reluctant to donate due to unsafe/unfamiliar donations channels available.   Solution  Our Crowdfunding Platform will be the solution to the problem by providing a safe and customer-driven platform to allow people in French West African countries to donate money through a secure and accessible platform.   Product   RaiseMeFunds will allow Africans in the diaspora and back home to donate money for personal campaigns and to organizations.   Customers & Feedback   According to customer discovery we have done, Africans in the diaspora and back home will tend to donate money through campaigns if the channel is secure and affordable. So, we’re targeting the West African community abroad and donors abroad to provide access to a safe product for them.   Market   In 2019, the global Crowdfunding market size was USD 13.930 billion, and it is expected to reach USD 39.79 billion by the end of 2026. African volumes in a variety of crowdfunding models reached $182 million in 2016, growing 118% from $83 million in 2015. From a regional perspective, 41% of these volumes have been recorded in West Africa, 28% have been recorded in Southern Africa, 24% in Eastern Africa, and the remaining 7% in North and Central Africa. We picked Ivory Coast to install our headquarters because Ivory Coast is number five in the fastest growing economies in the world with an annual remittance ranging from $340-$390 million dollars.   Business Model   RaiseMeFunds is a crowdfunding platform that simply allows anyone to raise money for social causes. Campaigns can be launched in various categories, ranging from emergencies to medical; Individuals, as well as teams and charities, are eligible to open campaigns on the platform RaiseMeFunds shall make money by charging users a fee for every donation they receive. These are called platform and transaction fees. The platform furthermore generates money from donations that users can make directly towards the platform.   Competition   Currently, Donate-ng is the only crowdfunding platform in sub-Saharan Africa focused on personal crowdfunding which is only implemented in Nigeria. We are going to have our offices in Côte d'Ivoire.    Value creation   Unlike the Donate-ng platform, we will be based in French-Speaking countries starting with Ivory Coast, and eventually move to Senegal, Togo, Benin, Burkina Faso, Guinea, Mali, where they are no existing crowdfunding now. Recently, a Nigerian based startup (PayStack), the only Nigerian payment processing company in Nigeria was acquired by the American giant payment processing company (Stripe) for $200 million. Just an example of how startups in Africa are progressing exponentially.  In addition, developing our personal secure payment processing system allows us to cut costs towards platforms like Stripe.  Sales and Marketing   Partnerships with telecommunications companies like (Orange, MTN) to facilitate our network and marketing strategy in Ivory Coast. We plan to work with local newspapers and social media experts to bring awareness to our platform. Currently, we are not able to predict any sales.  Investment Needed   In year one, we will need $10,500 for a server and maintenance, $20,000 for legal protection/Registration, $50,000 for an office, marketing, and HR.   Team   Jean Richard Loubao Kraka: CEO & Co-founder. Originally from Ivory Coast and Co-founded Innovative Apollo media, he is bringing his experience to RaiseMeFunds. Loubao has witnessed people struggling for paying their medical bills during his youth and decided to find a solution by working toe to toe with Elijah O.   Elijah Olasukanmi - COO & Co-founder. Originally from Nigeria, Elijah is the co-founder of Innovative Apollo Media, he has experienced the same struggle in Nigeria and he’s bringing his experience in product management, digital marketing, and business development from IAM and Microsoft to RaiseMeFunds to build a community that thrives and are connected.   Kayla Greene - Product Manager. Kayla is bringing experience in program management, operations, and analytics from SpaceX and Microsoft to RaiseMeFunds to help create quantifiable solutions for communities here and across the world.  Tani Makovsky - Business Developer. Tani is leveraging his expertise in business development, project management, and tech consulting at OurCrowd, CYC, and Deloitte to research and position RaiseMeFunds in the West African market.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US

Americans have lost faith in the news media.  Ovis was conceived to restore that trust. As current and former journalists, members of academia, professionals, and varied individuals from diverse backgrounds, the Ovis community has come together with a common purpose: to restore the public's trust in news.   Ovis’s tokenized publishing model allows members of the community to curate and validate content by voting on story selection, fact accuracy and editorial objectivity. Members purchase Truth Tokens (TRUTH) and use them to vote on which stories to cover and on the accuracy of the content. The higher-ranking stories are rewarded. The TRUTH Token also has the power to hold the people of Ovis accountable to themselves and to each other, which is the exact opposite way mainstream media operates now.  Ovis is the news reimagined.  Ovis is Journalism 2.0.

Description: Autonomous + EV for recreational boats.
Full Description: AllOY is bringing revolutionary tech, inside a revolutionary boat, to the $54B recreational boating market. Four barriers to entry artificially restrict the recreational boat market: Safety. In 2020, 767 people were killed and 3,191 were injured while on a recreational boat. That’s 2x more per-outing than skydiving. Hassle. The hassle of boating is often far greater than the hours on the water—prompting timeless quotes like, “The best boat is a friend’s boat”. Expertise. Lack of knowledge combined with fear of specific tasks (like docking and undocking) hinders adoption. Expense. Current operating costs include $400 per day in fuel plus unplanned maintenance, annual winterizing and de-winterizing, and marina-related expenses. We are starting from scratch and rethinking the way modern software, sensors, and control systems can (and should) change things to make boating easier, safer, and more accessible for all. AllOY is building a boat that docks itself, a boat that avoids other boats, a boat with a reimagined helm, a boat with an industry-leading EV powertrain and battery, and a boat that gets smarter over time. Our team includes a veteran founder with exits to broadcast com / Yahoo! and Gaylord Entertainment (Cotter), Co-founder & CTO, former Toyota Mobility CPO (Kinney), and board member, former MasterCraft CEO (Dorton).  Special note, co-founder & CTO, Dr. Kinney helped build the hardware and software solution that enabled his underdog, four-member team to successfully finish the 2005 DARPA Grand Challenge, a 130-mile, autonomous vehicle race across the desert.

Description: Run2Play is redefining exercise into a game by creating the next platform for mobile, augmented reality, and virtual reality fitness.
Full Description: Fit for All is a different kind of company.  We're not only building a better, more engaging fitness app where you can challenge your friends, compete in contests, and support charities with your activity. We're setting out to fix the broken app economy, and we've built the model and the infrastructure to build a movement across an entire ecosystem.   For us, this started by recognizing that it's the users that give apps their value.  Not the app's features.  Not their code.  The users.  Without users, an app is worthless.   Many apps offer their app to users for free in exchange for the right to advertise to those users.  So users get a free and convenient product.  But they give up control over their data, and all the value generated goes to the app company and the app company’s shareholders.  Those shareholders enjoy a significant multiple on user-derived metrics like monthly active users and revenue per thousand ads served to users.  So app companies work hard to maximize users' time and attention so they can acquire more data and serve more ads.  Users become the products, and are often subjected to psychological manipulation and other exploitation by app companies.  All in service to increasing value for shareholders.   Users can vote with their feet, but usually there's no better alternative and quite often there's no alternative at all.  So the preferences of users - manipulated in any event as they are - have little bearing on this system.   If users are a necessary condition for value, but users are exploited and have little to no control over the system that defines that value, then the system is overdue for a realignment.   So we asked ourselves some questions.  What if advertisers had to pay users to advertise to them?   What if apps were co-owned by their user communities?   What if users controlled their data and privacy?     What would that ecosystem have to look like?   What types of organizations are needed?   What do the relationships between them look like? And why shouldn’t the whole system prioritize our planet and a social purpose? If we were to build a single app to address these questions we’d bet it would not only be viable but could also inspire others to build new models and change existing ones.  And that would be a small success.  But a platform; a whole ecosystem of apps, united in a common commitment and shared principles just might be able to deliver lasting, systemic change.   Fit for All is a benefits company, committed to people, planet, and purpose, with ESG built into its DNA.  Run2Play is the fitness app created by Fit for All that will catalyze the ecosystem.   We created the AVA Foundation to generate and manage a token that can be used across an ecosystem of apps.  An adaptive reward engine allocates AVA Coin to users in proportion to their eligible activity.  AVA Coin can be used to purchase in-app advertising space, used for in-app and sponsor purchases, and traded among users and on exchanges, providing value and utility to the coin.  Each user selects up to three charitable causes to support, with the Climate Crisis preselected for all users, who donate 30-100% of their AVA Coin rewards, making seamless charitable giving a foundational element of the ecosystem.   While each component of the system is essential and complementary, the most innovative and important is the For All Cooperative.  Formed in Colorado, the For All Cooperative is a multi-stakeholder cooperative composed of users, app companies, the AVA Foundation, and investors, each in four distinct classes of membership, with the investor class limited in equity and voting power.  The app company membership agreement requires app companies to transfer increments of equity to the Cooperative proportional to Cooperative users acquired, up to 15%.  The app company membership agreement also obligates them to accept AVA Coin for advertising placements, in-app purchases, subscriptions, and other services proportionate to AVA Coin rewarded for user activity in their apps, also up to 15%, after which it is burned.  The Cooperative’s backend, Core, enables a single sign-on for all Circle Apps and an ad module that provides advertisers with anonymized but granular ad targeting for users who opt-in.  The Coopertive’s app, Conduit, provides social and gamification components to user-members, enables voting on Cooperative initiatives, as well as a marketplace for Circle Apps.

Below are some of My School Dance's top features: Online Ticket Sales- Sell tickets online for all your dances and events, receiving funds immediately in your bank account Eligibility List- Schools can maintain a list of email addresses for students who do not meet the qualifications to purchase tickets for a particular event, due to a disciplinary issue or any other reason QR Codes- QR Code is used to verify attendance and to alert parents via text when their child arrives and leaves the event Student, Parent, and Guest Permission Agreements- Event planners can generate custom Behavioral Agreements and Permission forms to be digitally signed by students, parents, guests, and guest admins Promotional Ease- Schools can promote the event with the enhanced link sharing functionality by sharing registration information to social media with just one click My School Dance was created based on the belief that school dances are fun and managing them should be easy. The best part? My School Dance is free for schools to use!
